parameters.text:
=Parse this raw Prometheus Alertmanager webhook payload and produce an investigation brief.

RAW PAYLOAD:
{{ JSON.stringify($json, null, 2) }}

=🚨 ALERT — investigate and triage.

Investigation Brief (produced by alert parser):
- Resource Type: {{ $json.brief.resource_type }}
- Resource Name: {{ $json.brief.resource_name }}
- Namespace: {{ $json.brief.namespace }}
- Symptom: {{ $json.brief.symptom }}
- Severity: {{ $json.brief.severity }}
- Status: {{ $json.brief.status }}
- Summary: {{ $json.brief.summary }}

Suggested kubectl commands: {{ JSON.stringify($json.brief.kubectl_commands) }}
Suggested PromQL queries: {{ JSON.stringify($json.brief.promql_queries) }}

Investigate now. Start with the suggested commands but adapt based on what you find. Run at least one kubectl command and one PromQL query.

Return your findings in this exact format:
SUMMARY: one-line status
SEVERITY: critical / warning / healthy
ROOT_CAUSE: your assessment in 1-2 sentences
CONFIDENCE: high / medium / low
RECOMMENDED_ACTION: specific actionable steps
REQUIRES_APPROVAL: yes/no

assignments.value:
={{ (() => {
  const b = $('Parse LLM Output').first().json.brief;
  const sev = b.severity || 'warning';
  const status = b.status || 'firing';
  const sevEmoji = status === 'resolved' ? '✅' : (sev === 'critical' ? '🔴' : '🟡');
  const statusLabel = status === 'resolved' ? '✅ RESOLVED' : '🚨 FIRING';
  return [
    sevEmoji + ' *' + statusLabel + '*',
    '',
    '🔧 *Resource:* ' + b.resource_type + ' / ' + b.resource_name,
    '📍 *Namespace:* ' + b.namespace,
    '⚡ *Severity:* ' + sev.toUpperCase(),
    '',
    '📋 *Summary:* ' + b.summary,
    '',
    '🤖 *AI Triage:*',
    $json.output,
    '',
    '🕐 ' + new Date().toUTCString()
  ].join('\n');
})() }}

=❌ *WORKFLOW ERROR — S3 Alert Triage*

Error: {{ $json.error?.message || 'Unknown failure' }}
Time: {{ new Date().toUTCString() }}

_Manual investigation required._
